cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language generation using neural networks. The use of recurrent neural networks and a Fourier-transformed color representation suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these sub-categories often deal with neural networks and image processing. Finally, the use of a large corpus of naturalistic color descriptions and the evaluation of the model's output suggest that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
